From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: SuperKali <hello@superkali.me>
Date: Sat, 18 Jul 2026 11:50:29 +0200
Subject: net: stmmac: dwmac-tc956x: read MAC address from firmware

The TC956x glue builds stmmac_resources by hand and never calls
stmmac_probe_config_dt(), so the per-port MAC is never read and each port
comes up with a random address every boot. The auxiliary device carries
the emac firmware node, and the Q8B exposes its per-port addresses through
an onboard EEPROM nvmem "mac-address" cell. Read it with
device_get_mac_address() into the stmmac resources, deferring probe until
the nvmem provider is up.

Signed-off-by: SuperKali <hello@superkali.me>
---
 drivers/net/ethernet/stmicro/stmmac/dwmac-tc956x.c | 6 ++++++
 1 file changed, 6 insertions(+)

diff --git a/drivers/net/ethernet/stmicro/stmmac/dwmac-tc956x.c b/drivers/net/ethernet/stmicro/stmmac/dwmac-tc956x.c
index 111111111111..222222222222 100644
--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/stmicro/stmmac/dwmac-tc956x.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/stmicro/stmmac/dwmac-tc956x.c
@@ -16,6 +16,7 @@
 #include <linux/pcs/pcs-xpcs-regmap.h>
 #include <linux/pcs/pcs-xpcs.h>
 #include <linux/phy.h>
+#include <linux/property.h>
 #include <linux/regmap.h>
 #include <linux/stmmac.h>
 #include <linux/types.h>
@@ -761,6 +762,11 @@ static int tc956x_dwmac_probe(struct auxiliary_device *adev,
 		goto err_put_mdio;
 	}
 
+	/* Per-port MAC comes from a board EEPROM nvmem cell on the PCI node */
+	ret = device_get_mac_address(dev->parent, td->res.mac);
+	if (ret == -EPROBE_DEFER)
+		goto err_put_mdio;
+
 	/* Put the MAC in a known initial state, then enable it */
 	tc956x_mac_init_state(td);
 	tc956x_mac_enable(td);
-- 
